<topic id="using-the-webhelp-plugin">
  <title>Automating the WebHelp Output</title>
  <body>
    <p><indexterm>WebHelp</indexterm><indexterm>command line</indexterm><indexterm>external
        process</indexterm><indexterm>outside oxygen</indexterm><ph keyref="webhelp"/> plugin allows
      you to use a command line interface script to obtain WebHelp output from DITA and DocBook
      documents. Note that the <ph keyref="webhelp"/> plugin is a standalone product with its own
      licensing terms and cannot be used with a <ph keyref="product"/> license.</p>
    <p>The WebHelp output files created with the <ph keyref="webhelp"/> plugin are the same as the
      output files produced when you run DITA or DocBook to WebHelp transformation scenarios from
      within <ph keyref="product"/>.</p>
    <p>When an automated process is required due to the amount of output needed, you must:<ul>
        <li>install the <ph keyref="webhelp"/> plugin</li>
        <li>acquire a <ph keyref="webhelp"/> license from <xref
            href="http://www.oxygenxml.com/buy_webhelp.html" format="html" scope="external"
            >http://www.oxygenxml.com/buy_webhelp.html</xref></li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
